item.dc:creator: @iScape0 iScape0
item.description:
@iScape0 wrote:

Silent How do i make my RSMV load the new models?

my main.java

[code]import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.InputStream;
import java.io.OutputStream;
import java.net.Socket;
import java.io.*;

public class Main {
private UnPack pack = new UnPack();
public Main() {
try{
}
catch(Exception e){}
System.out.println(“Runescape Model Grabber”);
System.out.println(“Thanks to Silabsoft”);
System.out.println("");
findVersion();
System.out.println("");
try {

    File mf = new File("./Models/");
    if(!mf.exists()){
	System.out.println("Models folder does not exist, creating it");
	if(mf.mkdir()){
	   System.out.println("Models folder created");
	} else {
	   System.out.println("Error creating Models folder!");
	   return;
	}
    }

/* Love from javacisnotrecognized */

        for(int i = mf.listFiles().length; i < 9999999; i++){

// if(i > min-1 && i < max) {//for grabbing a range of models
// if(i == ) {//for grabbing 1 model
if(i > 0) {//grabs all models
System.out.println("Sending request for Model: "+i);
addRequest( 7, i);
byte b[] = pack.unpack(download().buffer);
if(pack.unpacked) {
savemodel(i,b);
System.out.println(“Model Saved”);
}else{
System.out.println(“Model Grabbing Complete”);
break;
}
}
}
} catch (Exception e) {
System.out.println(e);
e.printStackTrace();
}
}

public void savemodel(int id, byte[] b){
        try {
        FileOutputStream fileoutputstream = new FileOutputStream("./Models/"+id+".dat");
        fileoutputstream.write(b, 0, b.length);
        fileoutputstream.close();
    } catch(Throwable _ex) {}

}

public static void main(String[] args) {
    new Main();
}

public void findVersion() {
    System.out.println("Grabbing Cache Version.");
    while (true) {
        try {
            System.out.print("Trying: " + version);
            if (connect(address, port, version) == false) {
                System.out.println(" Rejected.");
                version++;
            } else {
                System.out.println(" Accepted.");
                break;
            }
        } catch (Exception _ex) {
            System.out.println(" Rejected.");
        }
    }
}

public boolean connect(String server, int port, int version) throws IOException {
    socket = new Socket(server, port);
    input = socket.getInputStream();
    output = socket.getOutputStream();
    output.write(15);
    output.write(0);
    output.write(0);
    output.write(version >> 8);
    output.write(version);
    output.flush();
    int r = input.read();
    if (r == 0) {
        return true;
    } else {
        close();
        return false;
    }
}

public void addRequest(int c, int i) throws IOException {
	output.write(0);
	output.write(c);
	output.write(i >> 8);
	output.write(i);
	output.flush();
}
public CacheChunk download() throws IOException {
    CacheChunk chunk = new CacheChunk();
    byte dHead[] = new byte[3];
    byte jHead[] = new byte[5];
    input.read(dHead);
    input.read(jHead);
    chunk.cache = dHead[0];
    chunk.type = jHead[0];
    chunk.index = ((dHead[1] & 0xff) << 8) + (dHead[2] & 0xff);
    int s = ((jHead[1] & 0xff) << 24);
    s += ((jHead[2] & 0xff) << 16);
    s += ((jHead[3] & 0xff) << 8);
    s += (jHead[4] & 0xff) + 5;
    if (chunk.type == 2 || chunk.type == 1)
        s += 4;
    chunk.buffer = new byte[s];
    System.arraycopy(jHead, 0, chunk.buffer, 0, 5);
    int c = 5;
    int m = 8;
    while (c < s) {
        if (m == 512) {
            m = 1;
            input.read();
        } else {
            chunk.buffer[c] = (byte) input.read();
            c++;
            m++;
        }
    }
    return chunk;
}

public void close() {
	try{
		output.close();
		input.close();
		socket.close();
	} catch (Exception _ex) {}
}
private int version = 512;
private static String address = "world138.runescape.com";
private static int port = 43594;

private Socket socket;
private InputStream input;
private OutputStream output;

}[/code]

item.title: Rsmv help rep++ if u help
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

Sorry, Just gotta lol at you for having 116 rep and not knowing how to do this.

Okay.

RSMV (Runescape Model Viewer) is for viewing Runescape’s models which are extracted from the runescape cache.
Models are basically, EVERYTHING Runescape is made up of (Item looks, character parts, NPC’s, GFX’s, Animations etc.)

Models are used in RSPS to add models to a client, or even edit/recolour them in a program called metasequoia.

How it works is, if you go into your RSMV folder and look for a file called “Main.java”, and in there search for this.

private int version = 480;

Change the 480 to 512.
512 is the cache runescape is using currently.

Now, just below that, there should be something that looks like this.

private static String address = "world138.runescape.com";

BUT: Yours will probably not say world 138.runescape.com.
Whatever yours says, change it to exactly “world138.runescape.com”

Save the file. Close it, the go back to the RSMV folder.
Press compile… then c… then enter.
Press any key to continue.

Then press run.
This will then start extracting the models from the cache.
Note : This could take up to 4 hours to extract all 42.5k models.

Basically, after that, just press the actual RSMV program icon, then open the folder containing the models.
It may not respond for a second, as there is quite a lot of files.
After that, just search through all the models
Have fun.
Then you could try adding them.

Ok then, hope that helped.
It better have done.
